                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-352-person2922">
                  THOMAS 
                  BECH
               <interp inst="t18300415-352-person2922" type="surname" value="BECH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-352-person2922" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-352-person2922" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18300415-352-viclabel1906" type="occupation">silk-mercer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-352-victim2921 t18300415-352-viclabel1906"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18300415-352-crimeloc1907">Bishopsgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-352-crimeloc1907" type="placeName" value="Bishopsgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-352-crimeloc1907" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-352-off1904 t18300415-352-crimeloc1907"></join>. My young woman stood behind me, while I was showing some handkerchiefs to the prisoners, and after she had stood some time, she gave me some information, and not seeing some handkerchiefs which I knew I had laid on the counter, I charged the prisoners with taking them - they denied it; I sent for a constable- my young woman searched and found the handkerchiefs on them; these are my property - I believe there were no other persons in the shop at the time; I am not quite certain whether a little boy was not there.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-352-person2923">
                  SARAH 
                  HEATHER
               <interp inst="t18300415-352-person2923" type="surname" value="HEATHER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-352-person2923" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-352-person2923" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 1st of April I was in the employ of the prosecutor; the prisoners came in, and he showed them some handkerchiefs - I saw Rebecca Bradshaw take the handkerchiefs off the counter, and secrete them under her clothes: I did not see the other<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183004150150"></xptr>touch them, but she was close to her - I told what I had seen; the constable was sent for - he directed me to search 
               <persName id="t18300415-352-person2924">
                  Rebecca 
                  Bradshaw
               <interp inst="t18300415-352-person2924" type="surname" value="Bradshaw"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-352-person2924" type="given" value="Rebecca"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-352-person2924" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; I found the handkerchiefs concealed on her - she gave no account of them - they were perhaps a quarter of an hour in the shop - they asked for silk handkerchiefs.</p>


               <p>Prisoner Rebecca Bradshaw. This prisoner went to pay off something, not to buy any thing. Witness. No she did not.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-352-person2925">
                  JOHN 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18300415-352-person2925" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-352-person2925" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-352-person2925" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I went and found the property on Rebecca Bradshaw; I directed the witness to take it from her - there were five handkerchiefs in one piece, and two in the other; Rebecca said the other knew nothing of it - I found 8 3/4d. on them.</p>
               <p>Prisoner Rebecca Bradshaw. I trust you will have mercy on me; it was distress - this female is innocent.</p>
               <p>
            
